In a speech to Latino business leaders, President Trump expressed his commitment to unleashing the full potential of the Latino community by removing government burdens, restoring safety and security to neighborhoods, and defending America's interests. He touted the success of his administration in creating jobs, with nearly 3 million jobs created since the election. He also highlighted the record-low Hispanic unemployment rate and the strong performance of Latino-owned businesses. Trump emphasized the benefits of the tax cuts he signed into law and the reduction of job-killing regulations. He called on Congress to pass an infrastructure proposal and reiterated his commitment to securing the border and reforming the immigration system. Trump concluded by expressing his belief that America is experiencing the rebirth of the American Dream and commended the Latino business community for making America great again.